  <preface xml:id="meta_frontmatter-preface">
    <title>Overview</title>
    <p>
      <em>Learning Statistics with R-Instat</em> introduces the fundamental concepts of statistics through the 
      R-Instat statistical software. Designed for undergraduate students and other beginners, 
      the book combines statistical theory with practical data analysis using R-Instat's graphical interface. 
      It begins by introducing the R-Instat environment, data management, and data visualisation, 
      enabling readers to explore and analyse data without the need for extensive programming. 
      The book then covers descriptive statistics, probability distributions, sampling, estimation, 
      and hypothesis testing before progressing to contingency tables, <m>t</m>-tests, analysis of variance (ANOVA), 
      and regression. The final chapters introduce Bayesian statistics, providing readers with a broad foundation 
      in modern statistical methods while developing confidence in applying them using R-Instat.
    </p>
  </preface>

